               <p>222. 
               
                  <persName id="t18070218-52-defend579" type="defendantName">
                     WILLIAM 
                     FISHER
                  <interp inst="t18070218-52-defend579" type="surname" value="FISHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070218-52-defend579" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070218-52-defend579" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070218-52-defend579" type="age" value="23"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18070218-52-off275" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18070218-52-off275" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070218-52-off275" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               feloniously forging on the <rs id="t18070218-52-cd276" type="crimeDate">9th of February</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18070218-52-off275 t18070218-52-cd276"></join>, a certain order for the payment of money
            </rs> to the tenor following: - that is to say, February 9th, 1807. No. 76, Pall Mall. Messrs. Hammersley and Co. Pay J. and W. Lowndes, or bearer, forty pounds; signed, J. and W. Lowndes. With intention to defraud 
               <persName id="t18070218-52-victim580" type="victimName">
                  Thomas 
